data.content:
## EF Core Cosmos DB: Sync API Removal

In **EF Core 9** (.NET 9), the Cosmos provider started **throwing `InvalidOperationException` for synchronous operations** by default. You could opt in to sync-over-async behavior:

```csharp
options.UseCosmos(...).ConfigureWarnings(w =>
    w.Log(CosmosEventId.SyncNotSupported));
```

The EF team explicitly flagged this opt-in as **temporary**. In .NET 11, it's expected to be **removed entirely** — meaning all sync LINQ operators (`ToList()`, `First()`, `Count()`, `SaveChanges()`) on the Cosmos provider will throw with **no workaround**.

> ⚠️ .NET 11 is still in preview (ships Nov 2026). Confirm against the [EF Core breaking changes docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/ef/core/what-is-new/) for the final list.

## What to do

Convert all repository methods to async:

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key changes:**
- `ToList()` → `ToListAsync()` + `await`
- `First()` → `FirstAsync()` + `await`
- `Count()` → `CountAsync()` + `await`
- `SaveChanges()` → `SaveChangesAsync()` + `await`
- All return types wrapped in `Task<T>`

Callers must also be updated to `await` these methods, propagating `async` up the call chain through controllers/handlers.
